description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Team Lead Physiotherapist for Medical Rehabilitation and Frailty&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£45,780 - £51,393 per annum incl. HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Chelsea and Westminster Hospital&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a resilient and highly motivated Band 7 Physiotherapist to jointly lead the large Medical Rehabilitation and Frailty team at Chelsea and Westminster hospital. You will work across multiple wards and specialities to ensure that outstanding patient care is delivered, and will be a highly visible and key member of the wider therapies service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the day to day management of more junior staff within the team, and will be able to work autonomously to provide expert clinical input in a wide range of contexts. You will be responsible for the supervision and development of assistants, students and qualified therapists, and will work to ensure that our trust values are embraced by all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work, you will be encouraged to develop and progress in your career, and the trust actively encourages individuals to further themselves through both internal and external training opportunities. The therapy department has recently undergone a period of change with the introduction of seven day working, and alongside this you will be expected to actively participate in the on call rota and bank holiday working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think that you possess the skillset to thrive in a fast paced but rewarding environment, it would be fantastic to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michael Shaw, Clinical Lead Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;michael.shaw3@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07785325271&lt;/p&gt;
